sentences: Ta sai täieliku hinnangu oma töö kohta.
Me vajame täielikut selgitust sellest probleemist.
context: The word 'täieliku' is the elative case form of the Estonian adjective 'täine', which means 'full' or 'complete'. The elative case indicates movement out from inside something, so 'täieliku' can be understood as '(coming) from a complete state' or 'out of completeness'. It's used to express that something is completely done, whole, or entire. In English, it corresponds to words like 'complete', 'entire', or 'whole' when describing the fullness or totality of something.
